race.comment: Even race but sticking with ADALIE (7) who stormed home to score here last time. That was second run back and fitter again. Has won 2/3 this course and distance and has a strong third-up record so worth sticking with her off the low draw. BUTT HEADS (12) has been in top form winning last two. Big winner here last time in lesser grade but same rider aboard and drawn well. Can give a sight again. MEDALS (3) was placed in the bush fresh then poor there last time. Trained here and with a strong third-up record and back at home will take catching. CARRIBEAN KING (10) has been edging towards a win and is long overdue having been out of the winners stall for an age. Big run latest though and will be hard to hold out with a repeat. APUNTAR (1) is a smart galloper who was racing in far tougher grade up to a mile last time in. This might be a shade sharp but has the class for this company and will be storming home over the top.
